title: 820-00164 - S5 missing
message:
The board looks super clean, No liquid damage at all.
Here what happened:
PPBUS_G3H Was short to ground because of C7377 (PPBUS_S5_HS_COMPUTING_ISNS). I replaced and I got back PPBUS_G3H.
However, I don't have PP5V_S0 even PP5V_S5/S3.

[B]SMC_PM_G2_EN = 3.2V[/B]
[B]PM_SLP_S4_L = 0V[/B]
[B]PP5V_S5 = 0V
PPVRTC_G3H = 3.4V[/B]

Any idea?

title: 820-00164 - S5 missing
message:
No pulse at all at 5V_S5?
Check for short.

Post exact voltage for PPBUS_G3H and U7501; pins 23, 12, 13, 29, 21.
Do you get Magsafe light?

message: Are you sure PPBUS is restored? Measure voltage on pins 1 and 2 of F7140
